thread.title: Doncaster sale sets suburb record

author: Nicole Lindsay
title: Doncaster sale sets suburb record
text:
An off-shore developer has paid $7.2 million for a 1612-square-metre site in Doncaster, setting a new land record for the suburb.
Savills agents Nick Peden and Jesse Radisch said the price for 1027-1029 Doncaster Road, at $4467 a square metre was a record for Doncaster.
"We were expecting $6 million-plus," Mr Radisch said.
There was also strong competition at the auction of a former church in Elsternwick at 64-66 Orrong Road where a local developer paid $4.326 million, more than $1 million over reserve.
Advertisement Colliers International's Ted Dwyer, Jeremy Gruzewski and Tom Ryan sold the Uniting Church-owned 1756 square metre building, which has been used as an archive, at $2463 a square metre.
In the Montague precinct of South Melbourne, three bidders pushed the final price of a development site at 196-202 Gladstone Street to $3.155 million â€“ more than 20 per cent above its reserve.
The 435-square-metre site was sold by Colliers International.
